<h4><div class=3D"separator" style=3D"clear: both; text-align: justify;"><s=
pan style=3D"font-weight: normal; text-align: left;">DoseWizard</span><span=
 style=3D"font-weight: normal; text-align: left;"> provides a suite of rigo=
rously developed online tools for the conversion and estimation of radiatio=
n doses. The calculators are intended to support medical physicists, radiol=
ogists, researchers, and students in managing complex unit conversions such=
 as DAP to mSv, DLP to effective dose, and related measurements.</span></di=
v></h4><h4><p><span style=3D"font-weight: normal;">Our objective is to pres=
ent scientifically transparent, methodologically sound calculators that fac=
ilitate precision in radiological practice and research.</span></p><hr></h4=
><h2>Key Features</h2><h4><ul>
<li><strong>Comprehensive scope</strong>: <span style=3D"font-weight: norma=
l;">Radiation dose converters encompassing DAP, DLP, dose rate, effective d=
ose, and other essential radiological parameters.</span></li>
<li><strong>Scientific transparency</strong>: <span style=3D"font-weight: n=
ormal;">Each calculator is accompanied by underlying equations, assumptions=
, and methodological limitations to ensure clarity of use.</span></li>
<li><strong>Accessibility</strong>: <span style=3D"font-weight: normal;">To=
ols are freely available without registration, supporting both clinical and=
 educational applications.</span></li>
<li><strong>Professional relevance</strong>: <span style=3D"font-weight: no=
rmal;">Developed with reference to current radiological science and guideli=
nes, and continually refined for accuracy.</span></li>
</ul><hr></h4><h2>Explore the Tools</h2><h4><ul style=3D"text-align: left;"=
