Here is a straightforward CT dose calculator for determining the Effective =
Dose (mSv) from the Dose Length Product (mGy cm) for a CT exam of a single =
organ. Type a value in the DLP field to convert to mSv effective dose: &nbs=
p;                                   DLP       DLP unit                    =
  Gy.cm            dGy.cm            cGy.cm            mGy.cm            uG=
y.cm                      Patient                      0 year old          =
  1 year old            5 year old            10 year old            adult =
                     Body region                      Head and Neck        =
    Head            Neck            Chest            Abdomen and Pelvis    =
        Trunk            &nbsp;                      k (mSv.mGy-1.cm-1)    =
                  Effective dose (mSv)               The values for the con=
version factor that are used in the calculator are taken from the AAPM task=
 group report on Radiation Dose Reporting .
